Here are examples of Revit conflict resolution advice. Continue the pattern.

Conflict: James is moving the walls your Level 3 structural framing is hosted on — worth a quick chat before either of you syncs.
Acting: James | Modified: Walls on Level 3 | At risk: Structural Framing
Ask James to hold off on moving the Level 3 wall until you reposition your structural framing to the new location.

Conflict: Sarah is modifying the walls your Level 2 windows is hosted on — worth a quick chat before either of you syncs.
Acting: Sarah | Modified: Walls on Level 2 | At risk: Windows
Ask Sarah to pause the wall change until you adjust your Level 2 window placement.

Conflict: user-1 is modifying the walls your doors is hosted on — worth a quick chat before either of you syncs.
Acting: user-1 | Modified: Walls | At risk: Doors
Ask user-1 to hold off on the wall modification until you relocate your door to the updated position.

